WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.210 --> 00:00:01.620
<v Instructor>So here is a quick summary</v>

2
00:00:01.620 --> 00:00:04.380
on billing and custom tools in AWS.

3
00:00:04.380 --> 00:00:06.510
So the first one is Compute Optimizer,

4
00:00:06.510 --> 00:00:08.520
which allows you to get recommendation

5
00:00:08.520 --> 00:00:11.340
on resource configurations in order to reduce cost.

6
00:00:11.340 --> 00:00:13.830
The second one is the Pricing Calculator,

7
00:00:13.830 --> 00:00:15.720
which is allowing you to estimate the cost

8
00:00:15.720 --> 00:00:17.790
of services on AWS.

9
00:00:17.790 --> 00:00:19.830
The Billing Dashboard gives you a high-level overview,

10
00:00:19.830 --> 00:00:23.910
as well as a free tier dashboard to know where you stand

11
00:00:23.910 --> 00:00:25.680
on your free tier usage.

12
00:00:25.680 --> 00:00:28.530
Your Cost Allocation Tags allow you to tag resources

13
00:00:28.530 --> 00:00:32.580
to create detailed reports with your own tags as a filter.

14
00:00:32.580 --> 00:00:34.140
Cost and Usage Reports give you

15
00:00:34.140 --> 00:00:36.750
the most comprehensive billing datasets.

16
00:00:36.750 --> 00:00:39.150
Cost Explorer allows you to get your current usage

17
00:00:39.150 --> 00:00:41.700
in a detailed manner as well as forecast usage,

18
00:00:41.700 --> 00:00:43.140
months in advance.

19
00:00:43.140 --> 00:00:45.930
And Billing Alarms in us-east-1, they live,

20
00:00:45.930 --> 00:00:47.160
they allow you to track your overall

21
00:00:47.160 --> 00:00:48.480
and per-service billing.

22
00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:51.000
But if you want to get more advanced, you can use budgets,

23
00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:53.910
which allows you to track usage, costs, reserve instances

24
00:00:53.910 --> 00:00:56.130
and get alerts in real time.

25
00:00:56.130 --> 00:00:58.500
We get savings plan and they're an easy way

26
00:00:58.500 --> 00:01:03.150
for you to save on your bill based on long-term usage

27
00:01:03.150 --> 00:01:07.020
